<mjml>
  <mj-head>
    <mj-style> h2,img,p { margin:0; } td{ padding-top:0 !important; } p {margin-bottom: 10px;}</mj-style>
    <mj-font name="Roboto" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Roboto" />
    <mj-font name="Roboto+Serif" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto+Serif:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..144,100..900;1,8..144,100..900&display=swap" />
  </mj-head>
  <mj-body background-color="#f0f1f3">
   

    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
    
    <!-- Logo Header -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-spacer height="10px" />
      <mj-column padding="10px 12px 10px 12px" width="100%">
        <mj-spacer height="16px" />
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" css-class="light_img" width="150px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/logo.png" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" alt="" />
        
        
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 0px" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 2px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.4;
            ">Every successful company has a turning point—a risk that paid off, a product that redefined an industry, or a decision that changed everything. However, not every story is one of triumph; some of the most valuable lessons come from the failures and missteps that shaped the business landscape.</p>
          
       
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="0px 0px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    
    <mj-spacer height="10px"></mj-spacer>

    <!-- Bussiness history -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_fsection" background-color="#ffffff" css-class="mj_fsection">
      <mj-column background-color="#ffffff" width="100%">
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px 8px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="white">
          <h2 style="
          color:#8C3321;
            text-align: left;
            letter-spacing:6px;
            border-bottom:2px solid #8C3321;
            text-transform:uppercase;
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 300;
              padding: 18px 8px 10px 8px;
              
            ">A gamble that paid off</h2> 
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 22px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important;
            ">Daring experiment</h2> 
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px 12px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.businesshistory.co/email/images/bh-dec-28-1.jpg" alt="Daring experiment" href="https://www.businesshistory.co" />

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;">
          
           Jeff Bezos once confessed that Amazon Prime's initial projections were, in his words, "horrifying." When Bezos launched Prime in 2005, it was a bold and risky experiment. And yet, today, Prime has become a cornerstone of Amazon’s identity as the default online shopping portal. While Amazon's transformation from an online bookstore to the "everything store" is a well-documented journey, the story of Prime's inception is far less known but equally fascinating. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; filter: blur(5px)">The concept behind Prime was deceptively simple: for an upfront fee, customers could enjoy an all-you-can-shop, buffet-style two-day delivery on their orders. Amazon charged a $79 annual fee for the Prime service. At the time, Amazon charged $9.48 for two-day shipping, meaning it would pay for itself after just nine such orders. Bezos acknowledged that when his business team modeled the idea, the results were nothing short of alarming.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
  </mj-body>
</mjml>